title: Biltmore Oswald
creator: J. Thorne Smith, Jr.
description: LibriVox recording of Biltmore Oswald, by J. Thorne Smith, Jr. Read by Nigel Boydell. The hilarious diary of a young man's recruitment into, and service in a navy, which, though well equipped and disciplined, remains woefully ill prepared for his arrival and dubious contribution. (Introduction by Nigel Boydell) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (100MB)
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; adventure; fiction; humor
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: Good humor. Reminds me of the book, "Dere Mable", downloadable here, which is even funnier.

The guy sounds a little like like me in the Navy!

The reader of this humorous story is excellent with a really neat British or Scotch or whatever it is accent, but wouldn't it be better if he read stories that took place in England rather than the Bronx?  Anyway I like his style.  My favorite chapter was the mermaid chapter.   :)
